When the user says **Set up localization** or **Install localization kit**:

## Step 1 — Clone + install (terminal first; ask nothing yet)

```bash
cd "$(pwd)"
CACHE="${HOME}/.cache/CursorReactNativeAgents"

if [[ ! -f "$CACHE/localization/install/run-localization-setup.sh" ]]; then
  git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/codeandtheory/CursorReactNativeAgents.git "$CACHE" \
    || git clone --depth 1 git@github.com:codeandtheory/CursorReactNativeAgents.git "$CACHE"
fi

bash "$CACHE/localization/install/run-localization-setup.sh" "$(pwd)"
```

Then follow `.cursor/skills/localization-kit/SKILL.md` from **Phase 0** (or `$HOME/.cache/CursorReactNativeAgents/localization/.cursor/skills/localization-kit/SKILL.md`).

Do not hand-edit translation files generated by the agent.
